Governor Bala Muhammad, Dino Melaye, and other People’s Democratic Party (PDP) members were in Abuja to oversee the council election operations.


Governor Bala Muhammad
Governor Bala Muhammad and others were dispatched by the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) Party Chairman to monitor the situation at polling stations in Abuja.’
As part of my allocated responsibilities in my role as Sub-committee Chairman on the Gwagwalada election for the People’s Democratic Party (PDP), Abuja council election, I monitored the voting processes in the region,’ Governor Bala Muhammad wrote on his Instagram page. In addition, I was accompanied by Alhaji Hamza Koshe Akuyam, Bauchi State PDP Chairman, Senator Dino Melaye, Samaila Burga, and other dignitaries.
Below are some images from Abuja of Governor Bala Muhammad, Dino Melaye, and others.
On social media, many people applauded them for their unwavering support for their party (PDP).


